@speaker2: "...for me the first encounter of this concept was probably classical mechanics where we have this lever...so in this case...the lever, if we enlarge this lever...we can actually you know lift up heavier objects...this means that the input downward force is the same, but by increasing the leverage the output was increased by 3x...this is a very general concept.  it's a mechanism through which a small change or no change in input results in a larger change or a very large change in output."
