@speaker2: "...human labor is the oldest type of leverage...as an example let's think about a scenario where i want to build a pyramid...without leverage i would be building alone...and with leverage i can hire thousands of human workers...but the output is much higher because there are thousands of people working on this...the second type is capital...third type is more recent thing, especially more common in the bay area which is the code and software...if i write a code for an app, and then there's one user who gets value and let's suppose that number is positive. and while i'm sleeping, one more user downloads it and gets another value. so i'll put this double without me having to do any additional work...a lot of the recent value has been created leveraging this..."
