@speaker2: "...in historically large wealth creation...utilized these forms of leverage...the 20th century wealth creation...leveraged a lot of this capital leverage. and then recently, especially in the bay area, tech companies have leveraged the fact that if you write a code, the output can be multiplied pretty much indefinitely."
