@speaker2: "...if you have used deep research, that's to me the most well functioning ai agent as of now. there will be more probably, but that's at least the kind of the first working agent for me...and so that increases my output by a lot...so individuals are quite supercharged and this means small teams consist of individuals generating really big values...that's becoming more and more common. so in you might heard about startups with 10 people 20 people generating hundreds of millions of dollars of revenue...that's probably unimaginable 10 years ago...but now still uncommon but we're seeing this and i think behind the scene it's more of an ai acting as a leverage...previously if you want to increase the output then you again, you want to think about the leverage mechanism and after raising funds...then you have to really think about this human labor leverage...but human collaboration, especially at larger scale, has quite a bit of overhead...there's communication...it's a very difficult problem...just adding one person to 100 person group doesn't mean the output goes up by 1%. it can even be negative...now with supercharged individuals this overhead is becoming less favorable...we'll see more and more of smaller teams generating quite a bit of value...and more of companies might be of this size...and obviously there will be big companies but this might be a more common thing."
