st because of how experts have grown and the communication bottlenecks of many many people...and so these are i think the low-hanging fruits of ai acting as a leverage to advancing the science mission...but i don't think that's enough, we should probably go beyond and maybe just going forward we can expect advanced reasoning, maybe even better than human scientists and then ability to generate new ideas and knowledge...i think this is still rare and maybe i'm hearing some you know vague anecdotes that these are possible...but i think it can go a lot more than that and so i would expect that this kind of abilities emerge in the future generations of the model if not already in there and once that happens this will be you know just nonstop being research engine that works all the time and then they can work together across humans and agents and so on...this will be the main leverage factor going forward how ai can help this mission of the scientific progress..."
